"v.损坏 【英】 v.损坏(spoil the appearance of sth by damaging the surface) 【记】 de(变坏)+face(脸面) →把脸面弄坏→损坏 v. 损坏(外貌、表层、功用、价值或影响); 使变丑 = disfigure 【记】de不好的动作, face脸－把脸弄坏－使变丑 【记】de 不好 + face 脸→把脸弄坏→损坏 【相关】efface 更干脆，没脸→抹掉 deface (v.)  mid-14c., ""to obliterate,"" from Old French desfacier ""mutilate, destroy, disfigure,"" from des- ""away from"" (see dis-) + Vulgar Latin *facia (see face (n.)). Weaker sense of ""to mar, make ugly"" is late 14c. in English. Related: Defaced; defacing."
